# Auto-generated wasm wrapper crates for `examples/blinc_app_examples/examples/*.rs`.
#
# These are produced by the `tools/build-web-examples` codegen tool by
# walking the example source tree, finding files that match the cross-
# target convention (`pub fn build_ui(ctx: &mut WindowedContext) -> Div`),
# and emitting one tiny wrapper crate per discovered example. The
# wrappers are gitignored because they're 100% derived from their
# upstream `.rs` file — checking them in would be pure noise and would
# create a manual sync burden every time an example changes.
#
# Regenerate locally with:
#
#     cargo run -p blinc-build-web-examples
#
# CI runs the same command before `mdbook build` and copies the
# resulting wasm artifacts under `target/web-examples-out/` into the
# book's static output (see `.github/workflows/docs.yml`).
#
# `.gitkeep` and this file are tracked so the directory exists on a
# fresh clone — the workspace `members = [..., "examples/_generated/*"]`
# glob tolerates an empty match, so cargo doesn't error before the
# tool has populated anything.
*
!.gitignore
!.gitkeep
